  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      As a consequence of the increase in life expectancy, hepato-biliary surgeons have to deal
      with an emerging aged population, which has a potential higher risk for complication and
      worse long-term outcome. The investigators will be analyzing the liver function and outcome
      after right or extended right hepatectomy in patients over 70 years old.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
